The paper discusses a decision rule based on belief function theory, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve handling mass functions generated randomly and real databases, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM). The use of a distance measure also suggests a potential connection to signal processing (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
